HEADWORD: frilled
<hw>frilled</hw> <pr>(fr⟦icr⟧ld)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Furnished with
a frill or frills.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Frilled lizard</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a large
Australian lizard (<spn>Chlamydosaurus Kingii</spn>) about three feet
long, which has a large, erectile frill on each side of the
neck.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>frills</ent>⟦br⟧
